20 British motorcycle Grand Prix|GBR]]<br>{{flagicon|GBR}}\n! [[2020 San Marino and Rimini's Coast motorcycle Grand Prix|RSM]]<br>{{flagicon|SMR}}\n! [[2020 Aragon motorcycle Grand Prix|ARA]]<br>{{flagicon|Aragon}}\n! [[2020 Thailand motorcycle Grand Prix|THA]]<br>{{flagicon|THA}}\n! [[2020 Japanese motorcycle Grand Prix|JPN]]<br>{{flagicon|JPN}}\n! [[2020 Australian motorcycle Grand Prix|AUS]]<br>{{flagicon|AUS}}\n! [[2020 Malaysian motorcycle Grand Prix|MAL]]<br>{{flagicon|MYS}}\n! [[2020 Motorcycle Grand Prix of the Americas|AME]]<br>{{flagicon|USA}}\n! [[2020 Argentine motorcycle Grand Prix|ARG]]<br>{{flagicon|ARG}}\n! [[2020 Valencian Community motorcycle Grand Prix|VAL]]<br>{{flagicon|Valencia}}\n! [[2020 Spanish motorcycle Grand Prix|ESP]]<br>{{flagicon|ESP}}\n! Pts\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Grand Prix motorcycle racing}}\n{{World championships in 2020}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Grand Prix motorcycle racing|Moto3]]\n[[Category:Grand Prix motorcycle racing seasons]]\n[[Category:Current motorsport seasons|Moto3]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Motorsport season\n|series = Grand Prix motorcycle racing\n|title = [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Motocyclisme|F.I.M.]] [[Grand Prix motorcycle racing]] season\n|year = 2020\n|previouslink = 2019 Moto3 season\n|nextlink = 2021 Moto3 season\n|footer = [[2020 MotoGP season]]<br/>[[2020 Moto2 season]]<br/>[[2020 MotoE season]]\n}}\n{{MotoGP overview}}\n\nThe 2020 '''[[Moto3]] World Championship''' is a part of the 72nd [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Motocyclisme|F.I.M.]] [[Road racing|Road Racing]] World Championship season.\n\n==Teams and riders==\n{|\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|-\n!Team\n!Constructor\n!Motorcycle\n!{{Tooltip|No.|Bike number}}\n!Rider\n!Rounds\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Emilio Alzamora|Estrella Galicia 0,0]]\n!rowspan=15| [[Honda]]\n| rowspan=\"15\" | [[Honda NSF250RW]]\n|align=center | 6\n|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Ryusei Yamanaka]]\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center | 11\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sergio Garc\u00eda (motorcyclist)|Sergio Garc\u00eda]]\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Hiroshi Aoyama|Honda Team Asia]]\n|align=center | 79\n|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Ai Ogura]]\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center | 92\n|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Yuki Kunii]]\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Gresini Racing|K\u00f6mmerling Gresini Moto3]] \n|align=center| 2\n|{{Flagicon|ARG}} [[Gabriel Rodrigo]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/09/06/rodrigo-prepares-for-his-second-season-with-gresini/307240|title=Rodrigo prepares for his second season with Gresini|date=6 September 2019|accessdate=22 September 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 52\n|{{Flagicon|ESP}} [[Jeremy Alcoba]]\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|GER}} Leopard Racing\n|align=center| 5\n| {{flagicon|SPA}} [[Jaume Masi\u00e1]]<ref name=\"Leopard\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gpone.com/it/2019/08/24/moto2/filip-salac-al-posto-di-romano-fenati-con-snipers-nel-2020.html|title=Masia, Foggia form Leopard Racing Moto3 squad for 2020|date=10 August 2019|website=Crash|access-date=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 7\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Dennis Foggia]]<ref name=\"Leopard\" />\n| 1\n|-\n|rowspan=2| {{flagicon|MYS}} [[SIC Racing Team|Petronas Sprinta Racing]]\n|align=center| 17\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[John McPhee (motorcyclist)|John McPhee]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.motogp.com/en/news/2019/08/23/mcphee-signs-new-petronas-sprinta-racing-deal/305625|title=McPhee signs new Petronas Sprinta Racing deal|date=23 August 2019|accessdate=22 September 2019|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n|align=center| 89\n| |{{flagicon|MYS}} [[Khairul Idham Pawi]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.crash.net/motogp/news/930121/1/petronas-confirms-pawi-moto3-opens-moto2-slot-dixon/ |title=Petronas confirms Pawi in Moto3, opens up Moto2 slot for Dixon |date=25 August 2019|accessdate=22 Septe