{"title_page": "Emeraldella", "text_new": "{{automatic taxobox\n| genus = Emeraldella\n| fossil_range = {{Fossil range|Burgess Shale|Drumian}}\n| image = Emeraldella brocki USNM PAL 136439.jpg\n| image_caption = ''Emeraldella brocki''\n| image2 = Emeraldella brutoni 1.png\n| image2_caption = ''Emeraldella brutoni''\n| display_parents = 3\n| taxon = Emeraldella\n| type_species = '''''Emeraldella brocki'''''\n| authority = [[Charles Doolittle Walcott|Walcott]], 1912\n| type_species_authority = Walcott, 1912\n| subdivision_ranks = Other species\n| subdivision = '''''Emeraldella brutoni''''' <small>Stein, Church & Robison, 2011</small>\n}}\n[[File:Emeraldella brutoni reconstruction.png|left|thumb|reconstruction of ''Emeraldella brutoni'' ]]\n'''''Emeraldella''''' is a genus of [[arthropod]] known from the [[Middle Cambrian]] of North America. The type species ''E. brocki'' was described in 1912 from the [[Burgess Shale]].<ref name=\"Stein2011\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Stein | first1 = M. | last2 = Selden | first2 = P. A. | title = A restudy of the Burgess Shale (Cambrian) arthropod ''Emeraldella brocki'' and reassessment of its affinities | journal = Journal of Systematic Palaeontology | pages = 1\u201323 | year = 2011 | doi = 10.1080/14772019.2011.566634}}</ref> {{gpb abundance|21|< 0.1}} A re-study on the species was done in 2012.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stein|first=Martin|last2=Selden|first2=Paul A.|date=June 2012|title=A restudy of the Burgess Shale (Cambrian) arthropod Emeraldella brocki and reassessment of its affinities|url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/14772019.2011.566634|journal=Journal of Systematic Palaeontology|language=en|volume=10|issue=2|pages=361\u2013383|doi=10.1080/14772019.2011.566634|issn=1477-2019}}</ref>  A second species ''E. brutoni'' is known from the [[Wheeler Shale]], which was described in 2011.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2011-09-29|title=A new Cambrian arthropod, Emeraldella brutoni, from Utah|url=http://hdl.handle.net/1808/8086|journal=Paleontological Contributions|doi=10.17161/PC.1808.8086|issn=1946-0279}}</ref> Additional specimens of ''P. brutoni'' were described in 2019, which revealed more of the anatomy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lerosey-Aubril|first=Rudy|last2=Ortega-Hern\u00e1ndez|first2=Javier|date=2019-10-31|title=Appendicular anatomy of the artiopod Emeraldella brutoni from the middle Cambrian (Drumian) of western Utah|url=https://peerj.com/articles/7945|journal=PeerJ|language=en|volume=7|pages=e7945|doi=10.7717/peerj.7945|issn=2167-8359|pmc=6825744|pmid=31687274}}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n*{{Burgess Shale species | 51 }}\n* http://www.fossilmuseum.net/Cambrian-Explosion/Emeraldella/Emeraldella.htm\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3052157}}\n\n[[Category:Prehistoric arthropod genera]]\n[[Category:Cambrian genus extinctions]]\n[[Category:Wheeler Shale]]\n\n\n{{paleo-arthropod-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{automatic taxobox\n| genus = Emeraldella\n| fossil_range = {{Fossil range|Burgess Shale|Drumian}}\n| image = Emeraldella brocki USNM PAL 136439.jpg\n| image_caption = ''Emeraldella brocki''\n| image2 = Emeraldella brutoni 1.png\n| image2_caption = ''Emeraldella brutoni''\n| display_parents = 3\n| taxon = Emeraldella\n| type_species = '''''Emeraldella brocki'''''\n| authority = [[Charles Doolittle Walcott|Walcott]], 1912\n| type_species_authority = Walcott, 1912\n| subdivision_ranks = \n| subdivision = '''''Emeraldella brutoni''''' <small>Stein, Church & Robison, 2011</small>\n}}\n[[File:Emeraldella brutoni reconstruction.png|left|thumb|reconstruction of ''Emeraldella brutoni'' ]]\n'''''Emeraldella''''' is a genus of [[arthropod]] known from the [[Middle Cambrian]] of North America. The type species ''E. brocki'' was described in 1912 from the [[Burgess Shale]].<ref name=\"Stein2011\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Stein | first1 = M. | last2 = Selden | first2 = P. A. | title = A restudy of the Burgess Shale (Cambrian) arthropod ''Emeraldella brocki'' and reassessment of its affinities | journal = Journal of Systematic Palaeontology | pages = 1\u201323 | year = 2011 | doi = 10.1080/14772019.2011.566634}}</ref> {{gpb abundance|21|< 0.1}} A re-study on the species was done in 2012.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stein|first=Martin|last2=Selden|first2=Paul A.|date=June 2012|title=A restudy of the Burgess Shale (Cambrian) arthropod Emeraldella brocki and reassessment of its affinities|url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/14772019.2011.566634|journal=Journal of Systematic Palaeontology|language=en|volume=10|issue=2|pages=361\u2013383|doi=10.1080/14772019.2011.566634|issn=1477-2019}}</ref>  A second species ''E. brutoni'' is known from the [[Wheeler Shale]], which was described in 2011.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2011-09-29|title=A new Cambrian arthropod, Emeraldella brutoni, from Utah|url=http://hdl.handle.net/1808/8086|journal=Paleontological Contributions|doi=10.17161/PC.1808.8086|issn=1946-0279}}</ref> Additional specimens of ''P. brutoni'' were described in 2019, which revealed more of the anatomy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lerosey-Aubril|first=Rudy|last2=Ortega-Hern\u00e1ndez|first2=Javier|date=2019-10-31|title=Appendicular anatomy of the artiopod Emeraldella brutoni from the middle Cambrian (Drumian) of western Utah|url=https://peerj.com/articles/7945|journal=PeerJ|language=en|volume=7|pages=e7945|doi=10.7717/peerj.7945|issn=2167-8359|pmc=6825744|pmid=31687274}}</ref>\n\n==External links==\n*{{Burgess Shale species | 51 }}\n* http://www.fossilmuseum.net/Cambrian-Explosion/Emeraldella/Emeraldella.htm\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3052157}}\n\n[[Category:Prehistoric arthropod genera]]\n[[Category:Cambrian genus extinctions]]\n[[Category:Wheeler Shale]]\n\n\n{{paleo-arthropod-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hemiauchenia", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emeraldella"}
{"title_page": "2019\u201320 Hawaii Rainbow Warriors basketball team", "text_new": "{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |mode=Basketball\n  |sex=none\n  |year=2019\u201320\n  |prev_year=2018\u201319\n  |next_year=2020\u201321\n  |team=Hawaii Rainbow Warriors\n  |image=Hawaii Warriors logo.svg\n  |image_size=220\n  |conference=Big West Conference\n  |division=\n  |short_conf=Big West\n  |CoachRank=\n  |APRank=\n  |record= 17\u201313\n  |conf_record=8\u20138\n  |head_coach=[[Eran Ganot]] (5th season) <br> [[Chris Gerlufsen]] <br> (acting, November 6\u2013December 28th)\n  |asst_coach1=[[Chris Gerlufsen]]\n  |asst_coach2=John Montgomery\n  |asst_coach3=Jabari Trotter\n  |asst_coach4=\n  |stadium=[[Stan Sheriff Center]]\n  |champion= \n  |bowl= \n  |bowl_result=\n}}\n{{2019\u201320 Big West men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 Hawaii Rainbow Warriors basketball team''' represents the [[University of Hawaii at Manoa|University of Hawai\u02bbi at M\u0101noa]] during the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Rainbow Warriors, led by fifth-year head coach [[Eran Ganot]], play their home games at the [[Stan Sheriff Center]] in [[Honolulu|Honolulu, Hawaii]]. Hawaii is a member of the Big West Conference, and participates in their 8th season in that league. On November 6th, Ganot took a temporary leave of absence to deal with an undisclosed medical issue. He returned to coaching on December 29th for their game against Maine. First year assistant [[Chris Gerlufsen]] served as acting head coach from November 6th to December 28th, compiling an 8\u20135 record.<ref>{{cite web | access-date=2019-11-19 | url=https://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/2019/11/07/hawaii-basketball-coach-eran-ganot-step-away-team-medical-leave/ | title=Hawaii basketball coach Eran Ganot to step away from team on medical leave | last=Staff | first=H. N. N. | language=en-US | website=hawaiinewsnow.com}}</ref>\n\n==Departures==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Num